  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study was to evaluate the efficiency and safety of simultaneous islet-kidney
      transplantation in patients of type 1 diabetes with end-stage renal disease using a
      glucocorticoid-free immunosuppressive regimen with alemtuzumab induction. Islet
      transplantation can result in insulin independence with excellent metabolic control when
      glucocorticoid-free immunosuppression is combined with the infusion of an adequate islet
      mass. Alemtuzumab (Campath-1H ®) is a 150-kDa humanized IgG1 monoclonal antibody that targets
      the CD52 antigen. Prolonged lymphocyte depletion can be expected following alemtuzumab
      treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
